<p>Frank and Oak offer you an additional 5 percent off when you find the Easter eggs hidden on its website. All the more reason to click the companyâ€™s email and start browsing the sale.</p>



<p>While Frank and Oak prefer a minimalist Easter email,Â <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.forever21.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037729000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2H79iswacxBERhtKDwiJEA" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Forever 21</a>Â goes all-in on email design, accompanied by the subject line â€œAN EGG-STRA SPECIAL SALE <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f423.png" alt="ğŸ£" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />â€:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="642" height="856" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image7.gif" alt="" class="wp-image-118227"/></figure>



<p>The wordplay on the subject line aside, in this email, Forever 21 uses a colorful design with a GIF that screams Easter. The fashion retailer clearly gives its message with a bold headline that reads â€œ50% Offâ€. No more copy, images, or buttons needed.</p>



<p>Itâ€™s a typical Easter email you can model if design is your brandâ€™s strong suit.</p>



<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Offer a Limited-Time Deal</strong></h2>



<p>AlthoughÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/discount-strategy&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037731000&amp;usg=AOvVaw031F-Em8a2dfVWi6cGqTfu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">discounts</a>Â are effective in convincing prospects to take action, theyâ€™re not the only incentives you can use around Easter. Due to their natural urgency, holidays are ideal for runningÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/limited-time-offers&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037732000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1deYboI3ht4BFyUewmv3Iq" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">limited-time deals</a>Â that go beyond simple discounts.Â Whether itâ€™s a free shipping code, additional gifts, or a mystery deal you want to offer, make sure to limit it by time and evoke a sense of urgency.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.eyebuydirect.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037733000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2do59O8yY6r5cIYo1EphEg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">EyeBuyDirect</a>Â uses this tactic smartly and couples it with a classic example of aÂ <em>Buy One, Get OneÂ </em>offer:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="467" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-467x1024.gif" alt="" class="wp-image-118228" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-467x1024.gif 467w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-137x300.gif 137w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-380x834.gif 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-16x35.gif 16w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-23x50.gif 23w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-223x490.gif 223w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-220x483.gif 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image12-385x845.gif 385w" sizes="(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px" /></figure></div>



<p>Sent with the subject line â€œEaster Looks Made Easy,â€ EyeBuyDirectâ€™s email invites you to be â€œthe best-dressed in your family group chatâ€.</p>



<p>The companyâ€™s approach is clever, realistic, and relatable. They know how we celebrate holidays this year, so they try to create demand for their glasses by using this angle.</p>



<p>Although EyeBuyDirectâ€™s email does the job of promoting its limited-time offer, it could be improved with aÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/countdown-timer-popup-examples&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037734000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1VHhd4fDXPOpg3EN4MiAw_" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">countdown timer</a>. Especially because they extended this sale, thereâ€™s almost no urgency for a subscriber to shop. (Something to consider if youâ€™re planning to repeat EyeBuyDirectâ€™s approach.)</p>



<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Throw an Easter Egg Hunt</strong></h2>



<p>While seasonal sales and limited-time deals are all-year-roundÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-marketing-strategies&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037735000&amp;usg=AOvVaw0enevDsS1iYPkai-lbNR4v" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">e-commerce strategies</a>, thereâ€™s one little playful tactic you can only use around Easter, and thatâ€™s throwing a virtual egg hunt.</p>



<p>Donâ€™t get me wrong, I donâ€™t mean a full-blownÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/gamification-marketing&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037735000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1ISRQnkZy2YwHMO6Ntgk5l" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">gamified</a>Â online store experience. Iâ€™m talking about a simple mystery deal where you discount some of your products and position it as an Easter game.</p>



<p>Check out howÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.toofaced.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037736000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2h_4ztHvLtxascbZfpMybO" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Too Faced</a>Â runs an egg hunt and invites subscribers to play along via email:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="598" height="996" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118229" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8.png 598w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-180x300.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-380x633.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-21x35.png 21w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-30x50.png 30w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-294x490.png 294w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-220x366.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image4-8-385x641.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px" /></figure>



<p><br>Carrying the subject line â€œEASTER IS HERE! <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f430.png" alt="ğŸ°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />,â€ Too Facedâ€™s email, first, wishes you a happy Easter and then invites you to join the hunt. With it, the company simply asks you to visit its store and find its mascot on the website. Once you find&nbsp;<em>Clover,&nbsp;</em>you can reveal your surprise and find your â€œEaster treatâ€ (which is likely a discount offer.)</p>



<p>A virtual egg hunt like the above is a great excuse to invite subscribers back to your store by evoking curiosity.</p>



<p>Another brand that uses this tactic in their emails isÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.mancrates.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037737000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3cGfE-Hi0kLNQV3E2sYPri" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Man Crates</a>. Yet, the company makes it even simpler:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="737" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-737x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118230" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-737x1024.png 737w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-216x300.png 216w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-380x528.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-600x834.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-25x35.png 25w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-36x50.png 36w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-353x490.png 353w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-220x306.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2-385x535.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image16-2.png 749w" sizes="(max-width: 737px) 100vw, 737px" /></figure>



<p>In this digital Easter egg hunt, you hunt for Man Cratesâ€™ deals and find&nbsp;<em>egg-stra</em>&nbsp;special discounts.</p>



<p>Yes, itâ€™s just a sale. But instead of adding a sale label to its discount products, Man Crates cleverly makes them a part of the hunt. This way, you get a sense of accomplishment when you&nbsp;<em>find</em>&nbsp;a deal and likely grab it before itâ€™s gone.</p>



<p>In the email, the company also gives you a sneak peek at some of the deals, so you can click through and claim instantly, without even looking for them:</p>



