<p><br>While Poo~Pourriâ€™s email might work well on prospects who are actively looking to buy Easter gifts,Â <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://skandinavisk.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037740000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2RDumd1W44CmDJCao9_nJ6" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Skandinaviskâ€™s</a>Â approach can make you consider gifting your loved ones, even if you havenâ€™t thought about it before:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="645" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-645x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-118235" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-645x1024.png 645w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-189x300.png 189w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-380x603.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-600x952.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-22x35.png 22w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-32x50.png 32w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-309x490.png 309w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-220x349.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4-385x611.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image11-4.png 709w" sizes="(max-width: 645px) 100vw, 645px" /></figure>



<p>Sent with the subject line â€œSend a gift with some extra love this Easter,â€ the company positions its products as thoughtful gift options with this email.</p>



<p>While doing that, Skandinavisk explains&nbsp;<em>why&nbsp;</em>you should buy gifts for your loved ones, especially this Easter. To help you even further, the company also adds a gift to your order, to make it â€œextra lovingâ€.</p>



<p>Skandinaviskâ€™s Easter email, addressed by its founder, feels personal and it successfully promotes the companyâ€™s products without sounding salesy.</p>



<h2 id="6"><strong>6. Engage Your Email List</strong></h2>



<p>While a sale campaign or a limited-time deal can help activate yourÂ <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://sleeknote.com/blog/list-building-strategies&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1615464037741000&amp;usg=AOvVaw06aaCn8fH6XriFbtSw243t" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">email list</a>Â around Easter, you donâ€™t necessarily have to run a big sale to leverage this holiday.</p>



<p>You can engage your subscribers with an appreciative, subscriber-only discount code, or relevant, interesting email content.</p>



