<div class="wp-block-group is-style-shadow-box has-sleek-light-grey-background-color has-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<h3><strong>Action Items</strong></h3>





<ul><li>Write humorous or assertive empty cart page copy.</li><li>Add social proof by mentioning your happy customers or, even better, include <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-testimonials" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">customer testimonials</a>.</li><li>Create a website popup showcasing your most popular products and show it to visitors with empty carts.</li></ul>
</div></div>





<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Turn One-Time Purchases into Subscriptions</strong></h2>



<p>Youâ€™re likely familiar with the effectiveness of <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/upselling" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">upselling</a> and what it can do for your revenue.<br></p>



<p>Many online stores already use upselling and cross-selling to boost their <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/average-order-value" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">average order value</a>, but only a few experiments with finding new ways to maximize it further.<br></p>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/meundies-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">MeUndies</a> is an exception.<br></p>



