<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Collect Emails with a Lead Magnet</strong></h2>



<p>Capturing leads with useful resources is not a new strategy. But the good news is, you donâ€™t need to start a blog to grow your email list with lead magnets.</p>



<p>Lead magnets are a fair deal: Marketers grow their email list, and users get access to valuable information in exchange for their email addresses.</p>



<p>However, itâ€™s only fair if your lead magnet is <em>truly </em>valuable.</p>



<p>Cheat your prospects with low-quality gated content, and youâ€™ll lose them to a competitor. But offer them a genuine helping hand, and youâ€™ll likely convert them into customers.</p>



<p>Copenhagen-based marketing agency, <a href="https://obsidian.dk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Obsidian Digital</a>, knows this well. Thatâ€™s why they set expectations about their resources in this lead ad:</p>



