<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>(Get 24 concrete tips for better SEO rankings.)</em></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>







<p>With this Facebook lead ad, Obsidian captures email addresses of prospects who are interested in SEO, which is a target group for the company, and users get instant access to a valuable resource.</p>



<p>Notice how the company uses bullets and emojis to tease whatâ€™s inside the lead magnet and evokes curiosity with numbers.</p>



<p>At Sleeknote, we use a similar strategy when promoting our <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/content-upgrades" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">content upgrades</a> with Facebook lead ads:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="925" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png" alt="Sleeknote Facebook Lead Ad" class="wp-image-91460" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-195x300.png 195w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-380x586.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-23x35.png 23w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-32x50.png 32w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-318x490.png 318w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-220x339.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad-385x594.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Based on our experience, the key is, testing different angles in your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/copywriting-examples" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">copywriting</a> and creatives to find out what works best for your target audience.</p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>







<h2 id="5"><strong>5. Increase Event Registrations</strong></h2>



<p>In case youâ€™re not familiar with our marketing, we love hosting webinars.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="696" height="479" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Rikke-Excited.gif" alt="Rikke Excited" class="wp-image-91452"/></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>(Well, some of us more than others&#8230;)</em></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>







<p>One thing we learned from co-hosting 21 webinars is that promoting your webinars with paid advertising is the key to driving high-quality, targeted event signups.</p>



<p>But to drive more signups, we had to remove the obstacles for our prospects. Meaning, we started using Facebook lead ads to reduce the number of steps users have to take to register for our webinars.</p>



<p>And it worked as we expected.</p>



<p>Take a look at this recent webinar ad we ran on Facebook:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="525" height="753" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad.png" alt="Sleeknote Webinar Ad" class="wp-image-91464" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad.png 525w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-209x300.png 209w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-380x545.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-24x35.png 24w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-35x50.png 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-342x490.png 342w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-220x316.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Webinar-Ad-385x552.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 525px) 100vw, 525px" /></figure></div>



<p>The ad starts by asking a question that targets our prospectsâ€™ pain points and continues with a clear description of the event. The goal is to make sure that users know what theyâ€™re signing up for, and the video helps users with that, as well.</p>



<p>Hereâ€™s how the video looks:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="525" height="753" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Sleeknote-Facebook-Lead-Ad.gif" alt="Sleeknote Facebook Lead Ad" class="wp-image-91456"/></figure></div>



<p>By using only three input fields in the contact form, we made it easy for users to submit their email addresses with a few clicks.</p>



<p>Plus, we added an incentive for the first 200 signups to drive more registrations.</p>



<p>We ran two versions of this ad (in English and Danish) and targeted lookalike audiences of our existing subscribers who have a high <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/lead-scoring" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">lead score</a>.</p>



<p>If you want to follow a similar path in your lead ads, make sure to give a detailed description of your event and schedule your ads in advance.</p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>







<h2 id="6"><strong>6. Drive Brochure Downloads</strong></h2>



<p>Not all online businesses are the same. Thatâ€™s a given.</p>



<p>What works for one Facebook lead ad may not perform the same for your brand.&nbsp;</p>



<p>If youâ€™re not a direct-to-consumer brand, for example, not every marketing strategy applies to your business.</p>



<p>Unlike most e-tailers, you need to generate leads that you can hand over to dealers or resellers.</p>



<p>Whether youâ€™re a traditional retailer as described above or selling complex products with a longer buyerâ€™s journey, you likely use brochures to give detailed information about your products.</p>



<p>Since itâ€™s a common practice to deliver brochures in exchange for contact information, Facebook lead ads are the perfect medium to drive brochure downloads with hyper-targeted ad campaigns.</p>



<p>Check this example by the trailer company, <a href="http://airstream.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Airstream</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="900" height="866" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png" alt="Airstream Facebook Lead Ad" class="wp-image-91404" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png 900w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-300x289.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-768x739.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-380x366.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-600x577.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-760x731.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-36x35.png 36w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-52x50.png 52w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-509x490.png 509w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-220x212.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Airstream-Facebook-Lead-Ad-385x370.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></figure></div>



<p>With this lead ad, Airstream promotes one of its products by focusing on its features, using a carousel ad and videos.</p>



<p>This type of ad works great as a retargeting strategy to capture Facebook users who had earlier visited your site.</p>



<p>If you also have brochures with specs and technical information that prospects need to read before making a buying decision, promote them on Facebook, and ask for usersâ€™ contact information in exchange.</p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>







<h2 id="7"><strong>7. Collect Pre-Launch Leads</strong></h2>



<p>While itâ€™s common for car brands to use Facebook lead ads to increase test drive bookings, thereâ€™s one strategy <a href="https://www.nissan.ie/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Nissan</a> uses that is applicable to any brand.</p>



<p>The company uses Facebook to create excitement around their new product launch:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="602" height="938" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png" alt="Nissan Facebook Lead Ad" class="wp-image-91444" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad.png 602w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-193x300.png 193w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-380x592.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-600x935.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-22x35.png 22w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-32x50.png 32w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-314x490.png 314w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-220x343.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Nissan-Facebook-Lead-Ad-385x600.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px" /></figure></div>



<p>While doing that, Nissan goes beyond simply announcing an upcoming car model and asking users to â€œstay tuned.â€ Instead, they invite you to join their email list to be the first to know about this launch.</p>



<p>This way, Nissan collects email addresses of highly interested prospects that they can email during and after their product launch.</p>



<p>The best part is, you can easily replicate this strategy no matter what youâ€™re selling.</p>



<p>Whether youâ€™re launching new-season dresses, a new brand added to your collection, or your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/black-friday-marketing-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Black Friday</a> deals, Facebook lead ads help you generate buzz around it and collect targeted email addresses.</p>



<p>And if you want to make your lead ads more interesting, try adding some mystery to your copy and creative.</p>


