<h2 id="4"><strong>4. The Lowest Price Guarantee</strong></h2>



<p>Competition in e-commerce is real.</p>



<p>One way or another, you should make your online store stand out among the crowd.</p>



<p>And offering the lowest price is one of those ways.</p>



<p>In fact, price is <a href="https://www.bigcommerce.com/blog/omni-channel-retail/#why-us-consumers-shop-where-they-shop" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">among the top three reasons</a> why Americans choose to buy a product at a certain online store.</p>



<p>Offering the lowest price guarantee gives site visitors a strong reason to buy from youâ€”without even considering alternatives.</p>



<p>This type of guarantee shows that you are confident in your online store and the fair pricing of your products.</p>



<p>When you offer a lowest price guarantee on your site, you address many visitor concerns â€¦ including those who wonder if they can find the same product somewhere else for a cheaper price.</p>



<p>The lowest price advantage makes you stronger vis-Ã -vis competitors and improves your conversion rates.</p>



<p>You probably came across a few e-commerce sites offering to pay the difference if you see the same product somewhere else at a cheaper price.</p>



<p>But <a href="https://www.evo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">evo</a> goes the extra mile and shows how much they trust their prices:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="535" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-1024x535.png" alt="evo Price Guarantee" class="wp-image-92093" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-1024x535.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-300x157.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-768x401.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-380x199.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-600x314.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-760x397.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-67x35.png 67w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-96x50.png 96w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-740x387.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-220x115.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee-385x201.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Guarantee.png 1274w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you visit a product page on their site, youâ€™ll see a tag that says â€œLowest Price Guarantee.â€</p>



<p>Hereâ€™s what their guarantee looks like in detail:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="723" height="216" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy.png" alt="evo Price Match Policy" class="wp-image-92097" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy.png 723w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-300x90.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-380x114.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-600x179.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-117x35.png 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-167x50.png 167w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-220x66.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/evo-Price-Match-Policy-385x115.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 723px) 100vw, 723px" /></figure></div>



<p>Instead of simply paying the difference, the company also promises to beat the price by 5%.</p>



<p>This means higher self-confidence and a stronger focus on customer satisfaction.</p>



<p>If youâ€™re offering a lowest price guarantee on your e-commerce site, make sure you make it visible on <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/product-page-optimization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">product pages</a> and explain clearly what your guarantee covers.</p>





<h2 id="5"><strong>5. The Happiness Guarantee</strong></h2>



<p>If youâ€™re in e-commerce, Iâ€™m sure youâ€™re working hard to make your customers happyâ€”and hopefully, to keep them happy.</p>



<p>Because happy customers become <em>loyal </em>customers.</p>



<p>In fact, <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-statistics" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">30% of consumers</a> say that they would prefer to shop from a site theyâ€™ve previously bought from.</p>



<p>In Guarantee #3 above, we covered how important it is to make a good first impression.</p>



<p>But how can you go beyond the first time and ensure customer happiness in every single purchase?</p>



<p><em>Offer a happiness guarantee.</em></p>



<p>Hereâ€™s how <a href="https://bombas.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Bombas</a> approaches customer satisfaction the right way:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="976" height="390" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee.png" alt="Bombas Happiness Guarantee" class="wp-image-92081" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee.png 976w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-300x120.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-768x307.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-380x152.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-600x240.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-760x304.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-88x35.png 88w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-125x50.png 125w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-740x296.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-220x88.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Bombas-Happiness-Guarantee-385x154.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 976px) 100vw, 976px" /></figure></div>



<p>Taking a more sentimental position, Bombas frames their product guarantee around the word <em>happiness.</em></p>



<p>Instead of calling it a money-back guarantee or a full refund policy, they explain how important customer happiness is to them.</p>



<p>They stress that itâ€™s a <em>no-questions-asked </em>type of guarantee and theyâ€™re dedicated to solving your problemâ€”doing whatever it takes.</p>



<p>What I like the most in this example is the balance between <em>emotions </em>and <em>logic.&nbsp;</em></p>



<p>They donâ€™t only praise the customers and talk about how much they care about you.</p>



<p>And they donâ€™t simply write down a technical explanation about what you should expect when you want a refund.</p>



<p>Instead, they find a nice balance to make their brand trustworthy and keep their customers 100% happy.</p>



<p>If youâ€™re offering a money-back guarantee on your e-commerce site, try framing it around positive feelings and use <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/power-words" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">power words</a><em>.</em></p>





<h2 id="6"><strong>6. The Fun Guarantee</strong></h2>



<p>Nope, Iâ€™m not talking about guaranteeing fun to your customers. (Unless thatâ€™s your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/value-proposition" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">value proposition</a>.)</p>



<p>While looking for examples for this blog post, Iâ€™ve seen so many companies using a refund policy, just because they <em>had to.</em></p>



<p>Whatâ€™s the point of having a strong guarantee if none of your potential customers will see it?</p>



<p>If youâ€™re offering a satisfaction guarantee on your e-commerce site, you want to make sure that your visitors are aware of it.</p>



<p>So why not make it a little more attention-grabbing?</p>



<p>Thatâ€™s exactly what <a href="https://sunski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Sunski</a> does.</p>



<p>When weâ€™re buying glasses, we might think about what happens if lenses get a scratch or if the frame breaks. And Sunski knows our concerns well.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Thatâ€™s why they address customer pain-points and possible post-purchase problems in their guarantee.</p>



<p>And the best part? They donâ€™t write a page long refund policy.</p>



<p><strong>Instead, they create a song out of it:</strong></p>



